(6, 'Technology Overview', '# ⚙️ Technology Overview\n\n## 💻 Frontend Technologies\n- **React.js** – Used to build a dynamic and interactive user interface with component-based architecture.  \n- **TypeScript / JavaScript (ES6+)** – Adds logic, interactivity, and strong typing for better code quality.  \n- **HTML5 & CSS3** – Provide structure and styling for the application layout.  \n- **Bootstrap / Tailwind CSS** – Used for responsive design and consistent UI components.  \n- **Axios / Fetch API** – Handle HTTP requests between frontend and backend efficiently.\n\n## 🧩 Backend Technologies\n- **Laravel (PHP Framework)** – Manages routing, business logic, and database interactions.  \n- **RESTful API** – Provides structured endpoints for communication with the React frontend.  \n- **Blade (optional)** – Used for certain backend-rendered pages if needed.  \n- **Middleware** – Handles authentication, access control, and request filtering.\n\n## 🗄️ Database\n- **MySQL** – Relational database for storing user, product, and transaction data.  \n- **Eloquent ORM** – Simplifies database queries through Laravel’s object-oriented model system.  \n- **Migrations & Seeders** – Manage database schema and populate sample data for development.\n\n## 🔐 Security & Authentication\n- **JWT (JSON Web Token)** – Used for user authentication and maintaining sessions securely.  \n- **CSRF Protection** – Ensures secure form submissions.  \n- **Input Validation & Sanitization** – Prevents SQL injection and XSS attacks.  \n- **Password Hashing (bcrypt)** – Protects user credentials.\n\n## 🧠 Development Tools\n- **Visual Studio Code** – Primary IDE for coding and debugging.  \n- **Git & GitHub** – Version control and team collaboration.  \n- **Postman** – For testing and validating API endpoints.  \n- **phpMyAdmin** – Manage and monitor the MySQL database easily.\n\n## ☁️ Deployment & Environment\n- **XAMPP / Laragon** – Local development environment for PHP and MySQL.  \n- **npm / Node.js** – Manages frontend dependencies and React build process.  \n- **.env Configuration** – Stores sensitive environment variables securely.\n\n## 🚀 Summary\nThis project integrates **React.js** as the frontend and **Laravel** as the backend to create a modern, full-stack web application.  \nThe combination allows for **fast, maintainable, and scalable development**, aligning with real-world industry practices.  \nThrough this project, practical experience in full-stack development, API integration, and secure coding is gained — skills that are highly valuable for future projects and the Final Year Project (FYP).\n', NULL, 33, 33, 33, 0, NULL, '2025-10-14 09:27:49', '2025-10-21 06:14:23'),
(7, 'Software Architecture Focus', '# 🧩 Software Architecture and Technology\n\nThe system follows a **3-tier architecture** to ensure scalability, maintainability, and separation of concerns.\n\n---\n\n## 🏗️ System Architecture\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n  A[Frontend: React.js] -->|API Calls| B[Backend: Laravel Framework]\n  B -->|Database Queries| C[Database: MySQL]\n  subgraph Infrastructure\n    D[Local Server (XAMPP/Laragon)]\n    E[Version Control (Git & GitHub)]\n  end\n  D -.-> B\n  E -.-> A\n  E -.-> B\n', NULL, 33, 33, 33, 0, 'UPDATE', '2025-10-14 09:42:22', '2025-10-21 07:17:14'),
(8, 'Tech Team Onboarding Guide', '# 👋 Welcome to the Tech Team!\n\nWelcome aboard! We\'re thrilled to have you join our **Technology Department**.  \nThis document will help you get started with our tools, workflows, and culture so you can onboard smoothly.\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 1. Introduction\n\n### About Us\nOur team focuses on building innovative digital solutions — from backend systems and APIs to web and mobile applications.  \nWe value **clean code**, **collaboration**, and **continuous learning**.\n\n### Mission\nTo deliver high-quality, scalable, and secure technology that empowers our users and drives business growth.\n\n---\n\n## 🧭 2. Our Tech Stack\n\n| Category | Technology / Tools |\n|-----------|--------------------|\n| Frontend  | React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS |\n| Backend   | Node.js, Express, PHP, Laravel |\n| Database  | MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB |\n| DevOps    | Docker, GitHub Actions, Nginx |\n| Version Control | Git, GitHub / GitLab |\n| Project Management | Jira, Notion, Slack |\n\n> 💡 Tip: Familiarize yourself with our repositories and branching conventions before your first commit.\n\n---\n\n## 🧰 3. Development Environment Setup\n\n1. **Clone the Repository**\n   ```bash\n   git clone https://github.com/company/project.git\n   cd project\n', 2, 33, 33, 33, 1, 'UPDATE', '2025-10-15 01:53:45', '2025-10-21 08:51:22'),
(9, 'Policies & Guidelines', '## 🛡️ 21. Policies & Guidelines\n\nTo ensure a safe, productive, and professional environment, please review and follow these policies carefully.\n\n---\n\n### 📋 21.1 Code of Conduct\n\nWe expect every team member to:\n- Treat others with **respect and professionalism**.\n- Maintain a **collaborative** and **inclusive** atmosphere.\n- Provide **constructive feedback** during reviews.\n- Avoid harassment, discrimination, or inappropriate behavior.\n- Communicate openly and honestly.\n\n> 🚨 Any form of disrespect or misconduct will not be tolerated and should be reported to your supervisor or HR.\n\n---\n\n### 🔐 21.2 Data Privacy & Security Policy\n\n- Do **not share** user data or internal files outside the company.\n- Store all credentials in **environment files (.env)** — never commit them to Git.\n- Use **strong, unique passwords** for all accounts.\n- Always use **company-approved tools** for file sharing.\n- Follow **GDPR** and local privacy laws when handling user data.\n\n> ⚠️ Example: Never upload database dumps to public repositories.\n\n---\n\n### 🧠 21.3 Intellectual Property Policy\n\n- All code, designs, and assets created during your work belong to the company/project.\n- You may not reuse or distribute project materials without written permission.\n- Respect open-source licenses when using third-party libraries.\n\n> 💡 Always credit external sources and follow proper licensing terms.\n\n---\n\n### 💻 21.4 Device & Network Usage\n\n- Company or personal devices used for work must have updated antivirus software.\n- Connect only to **secure networks (VPN if required)**.\n- Avoid using public Wi-Fi for sensitive work.\n- Do not install unapproved software on company machines.\n\n---\n\n### 📧 21.5 Communication Policy\n\n- Use **professional and respectful tone** in all channels.\n- Keep discussions in appropriate Slack channels (e.g., `#dev-team`, `#design`, `#announcements`).\n- Avoid sharing sensitive project info via personal email or DMs.\n- Meetings should be scheduled via official calendar tools.\n\n---\n\n### 🕐 21.6 Working Hours & Availability\n\n| Policy | Detail |\n|--------|---------|\n| Standard Hours | 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM (Mon–Fri) |\n| Flexible Hours | Allowed with supervisor approval |\n| Overtime | Must be pre-approved |\n| Remote Work | Available depending on role |\n\n> 🧭 Always update your Slack status if you’re away or unavailable.\n\n---\n\n### 🧩 21.7 Code Review & Merge Policy\n\n1. Every PR must have **at least one reviewer approval**.  \n2. **Self-merging** is allowed only for small, non-breaking changes (e.g., documentation).  \n3. Follow our **branch naming conventions** (`feature/`, `fix/`, `hotfix/`).  \n4. **No direct pushes** to `main` or `production` branches.\n\n---\n\n### 🧾 21.8 Documentation Policy\n\n- All new features or major changes must include documentation updates.\n- Use Markdown format and store docs in `/docs` or Notion.\n- Keep README files up to date with setup instructions.\n- Add inline comments for complex functions or logic.\n\n---\n\n### 🧯 21.9 Incident Response Policy\n\nIn case of a system failure or security breach:\n1. Notify your **team lead or DevOps** immediately.\n2. Record details (error logs, time, affected modules).\n3. Avoid making public statements until approved.\n4. Document the fix after resolution.\n\n> 🔔 Emergency contact: `devops@company.com`\n\n---\n\n### 🎓 21.10 Learning & Development Policy\n\n- You are encouraged to attend workshops, hackathons, or online courses.\n- Training expenses may be reimbursed upon approval.\n- Share new learnings with the team in knowledge-sharing sessions.\n\n---\n\n### 💬 21.11 Confidentiality Policy\n\n- All internal information, including project roadmaps, clients, and financial data, is **strictly confidential**.\n- Discussing internal details on social media or external forums is **prohibited**.\n- Non-disclosure agreements (NDAs) must be respected at all times.\n\n---\n\n### 🧾 21.12 Compliance Policy\n\nAll team members must comply with:\n- **Local labor laws and digital regulations**\n- **Company code of ethics**\n- **Open-source license compliance**\n- **Security audit requirements**\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Policy Acknowledgement\n\nBy continuing to work on this project, you confirm that you have read and understood the above policies and agree to comply with them at all times.\n\n> 📄 _For questions or clarifications, contact your team lead or HR representative._\n', 6, 33, 33, 33, 1, 'UPDATE', '2025-10-15 02:08:28', '2025-10-22 02:07:38'),
(10, 'Tech Policies', '## ⚖️ 22. Extended Tech Policies\n\nIn addition to general workplace rules, the following policies apply specifically to the Technology Department.  \nThese ensure consistency, security, and professionalism across all development activities.\n\n---\n\n### 🧱 22.1 Code Quality Policy\n\nWe are committed to maintaining clean, maintainable, and scalable codebases.\n\n#### Guidelines:\n- Follow established style guides (ESLint, PEP8, PSR-12, etc.).\n- Enforce linting and formatting before every commit.\n- Write **unit tests** for core functions.\n- Avoid code duplication — reuse existing components or utilities.\n- Review others’ code respectfully and constructively.\n\n> ✅ Aim for readability first, optimization second.\n\n---\n\n### 🧩 22.2 Branching & Release Policy\n\nTo keep our workflow consistent, all projects must follow **GitFlow** or **Trunk-Based Development** (depending on project type).\n\n#### Branch Types:\n| Branch | Purpose |\n|--------|----------|\n| `main` / `master` | Stable production code |\n| `develop` | Ongoing development branch |\n| `feature/*` | New features |\n| `fix/*` | Bug fixes |\n| `hotfix/*` | Urgent production fixes |\n| `release/*` | Pre-release testing |\n\n#### Rules:\n- Never commit directly to `main`.  \n- Merge via Pull Request only.  \n- Tag every production release (e.g. `v1.0.3`).\n\n---\n\n### 🔐 22.3 Security Policy (Technical)\n\n#### Passwords & Access:\n- Use **password managers** (e.g., Bitwarden, 1Password).  \n- Rotate credentials every 90 days.  \n- Enable **2FA** wherever possible.  \n- Access to production servers requires VPN approval.\n\n#### Secure Coding Practices:\n- Validate all user input.\n- Sanitize database queries (use prepared statements).\n- Never log sensitive data (passwords, tokens).\n- Review security alerts weekly (e.g., GitHub Dependabot).\n\n---\n\n### ☁️ 22.4 Cloud & Infrastructure Policy\n\n- All deployments must go through **CI/CD pipelines** (manual uploads are forbidden).  \n- Infrastructure changes require approval from DevOps lead.  \n- Monitor cloud costs and optimize resources regularly.  \n- Use separate environments for `development`, `staging`, and `production`.\n\n> 💡 Use Infrastructure-as-Code tools like Terraform or Docker Compose when possible.\n\n---\n\n### 🤖 22.5 AI & Automation Policy\n\nWe embrace AI tools responsibly to boost productivity while maintaining integrity.\n\n- AI tools (e.g., ChatGPT, Copilot) may be used **for learning, code suggestions, or documentation**, but not for:\n  - Generating confidential or client-related data.\n  - Submitting AI-written code without human review.\n- Always verify AI-generated content for accuracy and compliance.\n- Do not upload sensitive code or credentials into AI tools.\n\n> ⚠️ AI is a helper, not a replacement for human judgment.\n\n---\n\n### 💬 22.6 Remote Work & Collaboration Policy\n\nWe support hybrid and remote collaboration while ensuring accountability.\n\n#### Expectations:\n- Be online and reachable during core hours (10 AM – 4 PM).\n- Attend all virtual meetings on time.\n- Maintain clear communication in Slack / Teams.\n- Update Jira / Notion daily with progress.\n\n#### Tools:\n- Zoom / Google Meet for meetings  \n- Slack / Discord for communication  \n- Notion / Confluence for documentation\n\n---\n\n### 🧠 22.7 Knowledge Sharing Policy\n\n- Every developer should document their work and share insights.  \n- Conduct short **Tech Talks** or **Demos** after completing major features.  \n- Contribute to internal Wikis or documentation repositories.  \n- Encourage “learning in public” — share what you learn with the team.\n\n> 💬 Knowledge hoarding is discouraged — collaboration fuels growth.\n\n---\n\n### 📄 22.8 Documentation & Commit Policy\n\n#### Commit Rules:\n- Use **conventional commits** (e.g., `feat: add login form`).\n- Commit messages should be descriptive and concise.\n- Avoid “WIP” or “test” commits in main branches.\n\n#### Documentation:\n- Each project must include:\n  - `README.md` (setup instructions)\n  - `/docs` folder for architecture or API references\n  - Inline comments for complex logic\n\n> 🧩 Documentation is part of development, not an afterthought.\n\n---\n\n### 📦 22.9 Dependency & Version Control Policy\n\n- Use official package repositories only (npm, Composer, PyPI).\n- Avoid unverified or outdated third-party libraries.\n- Review dependencies monthly for vulnerabilities.\n- Lock versions (`package-lock.json`, `composer.lock`) to ensure consistency.\n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ 22.10 Disaster Recovery & Backup Policy\n\n- Database backups occur **daily**; code backups **weekly**.\n- Backups are stored securely in **offsite or cloud storage**.\n- Developers must not store production data locally.\n- In case of major outage:\n  1. Notify DevOps Lead immediately.\n  2. Follow the **Incident Response Plan** in `/docs/incident-response.md`.\n  3. Document all actions taken.\n\n---\n\n### 🧩 22.11 Open Source & External Contribution Policy\n\n- All open-source contributions must be **approved** by your team lead.\n- Do not expose internal project code or data.\n- Respect licenses (MIT, GPL, Apache, etc.).\n- When contributing externally, identify yourself as an individual, not a company representative (unless authorized).\n\n---\n\n### 🌱 22.12 Environmental & Sustainability Policy\n\n- Use energy-efficient settings on devices and servers.\n- Prefer digital over printed materials.\n- Shut down unused development environments.\n- Encourage remote collaboration to reduce travel.\n\n> 🌍 Small habits lead to sustainable technology.\n\n---\n\n### 💡 22.13 Innovation & Experimentation Policy\n\n- You are encouraged to explore new frameworks or tools — but test them in a **sandbox branch**.\n- Share experimental results with the team before proposing adoption.\n- All new technologies must go through **review and approval** before integration.\n\n---\n\n### 🧾 22.14 Audit & Compliance Policy\n\n- System access, deployments, and commits are logged and auditable.\n- Security and compliance audits occur quarterly.\n- Developers must cooperate with review processes.\n- Violations of data handling or security standards may result in disciplinary action.\n\n---\n\n### ✅ Policy Acknowledgement (Extended)\n\nBy continuing work in this department, you agree to comply with all technical, security, and ethical standards outlined above.\n\n> 🧩 _Responsible innovation = Freedom + Accountability._\n', NULL, 33, 33, 33, 1, 'UPDATE', '2025-10-15 02:19:55', '2025-10-15 02:20:52'),
(11, 'Testing', '\n# 🧪 API Test Documentation\n\n## 📑 Menu\n- [用户注册 Register](#用户注册-register)\n- [用户登录 Login](#用户登录-login)\n- [分类接口 Category](#分类接口-category)\n- [标签接口 Tag](#标签接口-tag)\n- [文章接口 Article](#文章接口-article)\n\n---\n\n## 用户注册 Register\n\n**Endpoint**\n```\n\nPOST [http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register](http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register)\n\n````\n\n**Body (JSON)**\n```json\n{\n  \"username\": \"testuser\",\n  \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"123456\"\n}\n````\n\n**Expected Response**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"message\": \"User registered successfully\"\n}\n```\n\n[🔝 回到菜单](#📑-menu)\n\n---\n\n## 用户登录 Login\n\n**Endpoint**\n\n```\nPOST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login\n```\n\n**Body (JSON)**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"123456\"\n}\n```\n\n**Expected Response**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"token\": \"your.jwt.token\"\n}\n```\n\n[🔝 回到菜单](#📑-menu)\n\n---\n\n## 分类接口 Category\n\n### ➕ 创建分类\n\n```\nPOST http://localhost:3000/api/categories\n```\n\n**Headers**\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\n```\n\n**Body**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"Tech\"\n}\n```\n\n### 📜 获取分类\n\n```\nGET http://localhost:3000/api/categories\n```\n\n**Response**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": [\n    { \"id\": 1, \"name\": \"Tech\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n[🔝 回到菜单](#📑-menu)\n\n---\n\n## 标签接口 Tag\n\n### ➕ 创建标签\n\n```\nPOST http://localhost:3000/api/tags\n```\n\n**Headers**\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\n```\n\n**Body**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"JavaScript\"\n}\n```\n\n### 📜 获取标签\n\n```\nGET http://localhost:3000/api/tags\n```\n\n**Response**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": [\n    { \"id\": 1, \"name\": \"JavaScript\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n[🔝 回到菜单](#📑-menu)\n\n---\n\n## 文章接口 Article\n\n### ➕ 创建文章\n\n```\nPOST http://localhost:3000/api/articles\n```\n\n**Headers**\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\n```\n\n**Body**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"My First Article\",\n  \"content\": \"This is a test article.\",\n  \"category_id\": 1,\n  \"tags\": [1, 2]\n}\n```\n\n**Expected Response**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"title\": \"My First Article\",\n    \"content\": \"This is a test article.\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 📜 搜索文章\n\n```\nGET http://localhost:3000/api/articles/search?q=test&limit=10\n```\n\n**Response**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": [\n    { \"id\": 1, \"title\": \"My First Article\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n[🔝 回到菜单](#📑-menu)\n\n\n', NULL, 33, 33, 33, 0, NULL, '2025-10-15 02:51:42', '2025-10-21 08:51:00'),
