(1, 6, 'CREATE', 33, '2025-10-14 09:27:49', NULL, '{\"tags\": [2, 1], \"title\": \"Technology Overview\", \"content\": \"# ⚙️ Technology Overview\\n\\n## 💻 Frontend Technologies\\n- **React.js** – Used to build a dynamic and interactive user interface with component-based architecture.  \\n- **TypeScript / JavaScript (ES6+)** – Adds logic, interactivity, and strong typing for better code quality.  \\n- **HTML5 & CSS3** – Provide structure and styling for the application layout.  \\n- **Bootstrap / Tailwind CSS** – Used for responsive design and consistent UI components.  \\n- **Axios / Fetch API** – Handle HTTP requests between frontend and backend efficiently.\\n\\n## 🧩 Backend Technologies\\n- **Laravel (PHP Framework)** – Manages routing, business logic, and database interactions.  \\n- **RESTful API** – Provides structured endpoints for communication with the React frontend.  \\n- **Blade (optional)** – Used for certain backend-rendered pages if needed.  \\n- **Middleware** – Handles authentication, access control, and request filtering.\\n\\n## 🗄️ Database\\n- **MySQL** – Relational database for storing user, product, and transaction data.  \\n- **Eloquent ORM** – Simplifies database queries through Laravel’s object-oriented model system.  \\n- **Migrations & Seeders** – Manage database schema and populate sample data for development.\\n\\n## 🔐 Security & Authentication\\n- **JWT (JSON Web Token)** – Used for user authentication and maintaining sessions securely.  \\n- **CSRF Protection** – Ensures secure form submissions.  \\n- **Input Validation & Sanitization** – Prevents SQL injection and XSS attacks.  \\n- **Password Hashing (bcrypt)** – Protects user credentials.\\n\\n## 🧠 Development Tools\\n- **Visual Studio Code** – Primary IDE for coding and debugging.  \\n- **Git & GitHub** – Version control and team collaboration.  \\n- **Postman** – For testing and validating API endpoints.  \\n- **phpMyAdmin** – Manage and monitor the MySQL database easily.\\n\\n## ☁️ Deployment & Environment\\n- **XAMPP / Laragon** – Local development environment for PHP and MySQL.  \\n- **npm / Node.js** – Manages frontend dependencies and React build process.  \\n- **.env Configuration** – Stores sensitive environment variables securely.\\n\\n## 🚀 Summary\\nThis project integrates **React.js** as the frontend and **Laravel** as the backend to create a modern, full-stack web application.  \\nThe combination allows for **fast, maintainable, and scalable development**, aligning with real-world industry practices.  \\nThrough this project, practical experience in full-stack development, API integration, and secure coding is gained — skills that are highly valuable for future projects and the Final Year Project (FYP).\\n\", \"category_id\": 1}'),
(2, 7, 'CREATE', 33, '2025-10-14 09:42:22', NULL, '{\"tags\": [], \"title\": \"Software Architecture Focus\", \"content\": \"# 🧩 Software Architecture and Technology\\n\\nThe system follows a **3-tier architecture** to ensure scalability, maintainability, and separation of concerns.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🏗️ System Architecture\\n\\n```mermaid\\ngraph TD\\n  A[Frontend: React.js] -->|API Calls| B[Backend: Laravel Framework]\\n  B -->|Database Queries| C[Database: MySQL]\\n  subgraph Infrastructure\\n    D[Local Server (XAMPP/Laragon)]\\n    E[Version Control (Git & GitHub)]\\n  end\\n  D -.-> B\\n  E -.-> A\\n  E -.-> B\\n\", \"category_id\": 1}'),
