(9, 10, 'CREATE', 33, '2025-10-15 02:19:55', NULL, '{\"tags\": [13, 1], \"title\": \"Tech Policies\", \"content\": \"## ⚖️ 22. Extended Tech Policies\\n\\nIn addition to general workplace rules, the following policies apply specifically to the Technology Department.  \\nThese ensure consistency, security, and professionalism across all development activities.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🧱 22.1 Code Quality Policy\\n\\nWe are committed to maintaining clean, maintainable, and scalable codebases.\\n\\n#### Guidelines:\\n- Follow established style guides (ESLint, PEP8, PSR-12, etc.).\\n- Enforce linting and formatting before every commit.\\n- Write **unit tests** for core functions.\\n- Avoid code duplication — reuse existing components or utilities.\\n- Review others’ code respectfully and constructively.\\n\\n> ✅ Aim for readability first, optimization second.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🧩 22.2 Branching & Release Policy\\n\\nTo keep our workflow consistent, all projects must follow **GitFlow** or **Trunk-Based Development** (depending on project type).\\n\\n#### Branch Types:\\n| Branch | Purpose |\\n|--------|----------|\\n| `main` / `master` | Stable production code |\\n| `develop` | Ongoing development branch |\\n| `feature/*` | New features |\\n| `fix/*` | Bug fixes |\\n| `hotfix/*` | Urgent production fixes |\\n| `release/*` | Pre-release testing |\\n\\n#### Rules:\\n- Never commit directly to `main`.  \\n- Merge via Pull Request only.  \\n- Tag every production release (e.g. `v1.0.3`).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🔐 22.3 Security Policy (Technical)\\n\\n#### Passwords & Access:\\n- Use **password managers** (e.g., Bitwarden, 1Password).  \\n- Rotate credentials every 90 days.  \\n- Enable **2FA** wherever possible.  \\n- Access to production servers requires VPN approval.\\n\\n#### Secure Coding Practices:\\n- Validate all user input.\\n- Sanitize database queries (use prepared statements).\\n- Never log sensitive data (passwords, tokens).\\n- Review security alerts weekly (e.g., GitHub Dependabot).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### ☁️ 22.4 Cloud & Infrastructure Policy\\n\\n- All deployments must go through **CI/CD pipelines** (manual uploads are forbidden).  \\n- Infrastructure changes require approval from DevOps lead.  \\n- Monitor cloud costs and optimize resources regularly.  \\n- Use separate environments for `development`, `staging`, and `production`.\\n\\n> 💡 Use Infrastructure-as-Code tools like Terraform or Docker Compose when possible.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🤖 22.5 AI & Automation Policy\\n\\nWe embrace AI tools responsibly to boost productivity while maintaining integrity.\\n\\n- AI tools (e.g., ChatGPT, Copilot) may be used **for learning, code suggestions, or documentation**, but not for:\\n  - Generating confidential or client-related data.\\n  - Submitting AI-written code without human review.\\n- Always verify AI-generated content for accuracy and compliance.\\n- Do not upload sensitive code or credentials into AI tools.\\n\\n> ⚠️ AI is a helper, not a replacement for human judgment.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 💬 22.6 Remote Work & Collaboration Policy\\n\\nWe support hybrid and remote collaboration while ensuring accountability.\\n\\n#### Expectations:\\n- Be online and reachable during core hours (10 AM – 4 PM).\\n- Attend all virtual meetings on time.\\n- Maintain clear communication in Slack / Teams.\\n- Update Jira / Notion daily with progress.\\n\\n#### Tools:\\n- Zoom / Google Meet for meetings  \\n- Slack / Discord for communication  \\n- Notion / Confluence for documentation\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🧠 22.7 Knowledge Sharing Policy\\n\\n- Every developer should document their work and share insights.  \\n- Conduct short **Tech Talks** or **Demos** after completing major features.  \\n- Contribute to internal Wikis or documentation repositories.  \\n- Encourage “learning in public” — share what you learn with the team.\\n\\n> 💬 Knowledge hoarding is discouraged — collaboration fuels growth.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 📄 22.8 Documentation & Commit Policy\\n\\n#### Commit Rules:\\n- Use **conventional commits** (e.g., `feat: add login form`).\\n- Commit messages should be descriptive and concise.\\n- Avoid “WIP” or “test” commits in main branches.\\n\\n#### Documentation:\\n- Each project must include:\\n  - `README.md` (setup instructions)\\n  - `/docs` folder for architecture or API references\\n  - Inline comments for complex logic\\n\\n> 🧩 Documentation is part of development, not an afterthought.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 📦 22.9 Dependency & Version Control Policy\\n\\n- Use official package repositories only (npm, Composer, PyPI).\\n- Avoid unverified or outdated third-party libraries.\\n- Review dependencies monthly for vulnerabilities.\\n- Lock versions (`package-lock.json`, `composer.lock`) to ensure consistency.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### ⚠️ 22.10 Disaster Recovery & Backup Policy\\n\\n- Database backups occur **daily**; code backups **weekly**.\\n- Backups are stored securely in **offsite or cloud storage**.\\n- Developers must not store production data locally.\\n- In case of major outage:\\n  1. Notify DevOps Lead immediately.\\n  2. Follow the **Incident Response Plan** in `/docs/incident-response.md`.\\n  3. Document all actions taken.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🧩 22.11 Open Source & External Contribution Policy\\n\\n- All open-source contributions must be **approved** by your team lead.\\n- Do not expose internal project code or data.\\n- Respect licenses (MIT, GPL, Apache, etc.).\\n- When contributing externally, identify yourself as an individual, not a company representative (unless authorized).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🌱 22.12 Environmental & Sustainability Policy\\n\\n- Use energy-efficient settings on devices and servers.\\n- Prefer digital over printed materials.\\n- Shut down unused development environments.\\n- Encourage remote collaboration to reduce travel.\\n\\n> 🌍 Small habits lead to sustainable technology.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 💡 22.13 Innovation & Experimentation Policy\\n\\n- You are encouraged to explore new frameworks or tools — but test them in a **sandbox branch**.\\n- Share experimental results with the team before proposing adoption.\\n- All new technologies must go through **review and approval** before integration.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🧾 22.14 Audit & Compliance Policy\\n\\n- System access, deployments, and commits are logged and auditable.\\n- Security and compliance audits occur quarterly.\\n- Developers must cooperate with review processes.\\n- Violations of data handling or security standards may result in disciplinary action.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### ✅ Policy Acknowledgement (Extended)\\n\\nBy continuing work in this department, you agree to comply with all technical, security, and ethical standards outlined above.\\n\\n> 🧩 _Responsible innovation = Freedom + Accountability._\\n\", \"category_id\": 1}'),
