(85, 9, 'SOFT_DELETE', 33, '2025-10-21 08:48:21', '{\"tags\": [], \"title\": \"Policies & Guidelines\", \"content\": \"## 🛡️ 21. Policies & Guidelines\\n\\nTo ensure a safe, productive, and professional environment, please review and follow these policies carefully.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 📋 21.1 Code of Conduct\\n\\nWe expect every team member to:\\n- Treat others with **respect and professionalism**.\\n- Maintain a **collaborative** and **inclusive** atmosphere.\\n- Provide **constructive feedback** during reviews.\\n- Avoid harassment, discrimination, or inappropriate behavior.\\n- Communicate openly and honestly.\\n\\n> 🚨 Any form of disrespect or misconduct will not be tolerated and should be reported to your supervisor or HR.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🔐 21.2 Data Privacy & Security Policy\\n\\n- Do **not share** user data or internal files outside the company.\\n- Store all credentials in **environment files (.env)** — never commit them to Git.\\n- Use **strong, unique passwords** for all accounts.\\n- Always use **company-approved tools** for file sharing.\\n- Follow **GDPR** and local privacy laws when handling user data.\\n\\n> ⚠️ Example: Never upload database dumps to public repositories.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🧠 21.3 Intellectual Property Policy\\n\\n- All code, designs, and assets created during your work belong to the company/project.\\n- You may not reuse or distribute project materials without written permission.\\n- Respect open-source licenses when using third-party libraries.\\n\\n> 💡 Always credit external sources and follow proper licensing terms.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 💻 21.4 Device & Network Usage\\n\\n- Company or personal devices used for work must have updated antivirus software.\\n- Connect only to **secure networks (VPN if required)**.\\n- Avoid using public Wi-Fi for sensitive work.\\n- Do not install unapproved software on company machines.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 📧 21.5 Communication Policy\\n\\n- Use **professional and respectful tone** in all channels.\\n- Keep discussions in appropriate Slack channels (e.g., `#dev-team`, `#design`, `#announcements`).\\n- Avoid sharing sensitive project info via personal email or DMs.\\n- Meetings should be scheduled via official calendar tools.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🕐 21.6 Working Hours & Availability\\n\\n| Policy | Detail |\\n|--------|---------|\\n| Standard Hours | 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM (Mon–Fri) |\\n| Flexible Hours | Allowed with supervisor approval |\\n| Overtime | Must be pre-approved |\\n| Remote Work | Available depending on role |\\n\\n> 🧭 Always update your Slack status if you’re away or unavailable.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🧩 21.7 Code Review & Merge Policy\\n\\n1. Every PR must have **at least one reviewer approval**.  \\n2. **Self-merging** is allowed only for small, non-breaking changes (e.g., documentation).  \\n3. Follow our **branch naming conventions** (`feature/`, `fix/`, `hotfix/`).  \\n4. **No direct pushes** to `main` or `production` branches.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🧾 21.8 Documentation Policy\\n\\n- All new features or major changes must include documentation updates.\\n- Use Markdown format and store docs in `/docs` or Notion.\\n- Keep README files up to date with setup instructions.\\n- Add inline comments for complex functions or logic.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🧯 21.9 Incident Response Policy\\n\\nIn case of a system failure or security breach:\\n1. Notify your **team lead or DevOps** immediately.\\n2. Record details (error logs, time, affected modules).\\n3. Avoid making public statements until approved.\\n4. Document the fix after resolution.\\n\\n> 🔔 Emergency contact: `devops@company.com`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🎓 21.10 Learning & Development Policy\\n\\n- You are encouraged to attend workshops, hackathons, or online courses.\\n- Training expenses may be reimbursed upon approval.\\n- Share new learnings with the team in knowledge-sharing sessions.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 💬 21.11 Confidentiality Policy\\n\\n- All internal information, including project roadmaps, clients, and financial data, is **strictly confidential**.\\n- Discussing internal details on social media or external forums is **prohibited**.\\n- Non-disclosure agreements (NDAs) must be respected at all times.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 🧾 21.12 Compliance Policy\\n\\nAll team members must comply with:\\n- **Local labor laws and digital regulations**\\n- **Company code of ethics**\\n- **Open-source license compliance**\\n- **Security audit requirements**\\n\\n---\\n\\n## ✅ Policy Acknowledgement\\n\\nBy continuing to work on this project, you confirm that you have read and understood the above policies and agree to comply with them at all times.\\n\\n> 📄 _For questions or clarifications, contact your team lead or HR representative._\\n\", \"category_id\": 6}', '{\"is_active\": false}'),
